xbrl.ferc:DisclosureOfHowRespondentCalculates: System Lambda is determined by simultaneously solving incremental cost equations for each unit. Incremental cost equations are based on the first derivative of the input/output equation or heat rate. Coefficients in incremental cost equations are determined by one of two methods dependent on plant ownership. The coefficients for utility owned plants are based on heat rate data. Coefficients for independently owned units are based on fuel, variable O&M, and fixed O&M as stated in contract.
